parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: I live in the village of Ñangali.

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: I had a little child who was malnourished,

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: they used to give us food,

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: I went to get the food

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: the nurses from Ñangali’s medical centre,

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: ‘Ok, we will give you but only if you get ligated,

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: if you don’t we won’t give you food

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: because you have too many children,

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: and don’t want to get ligated.

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: And when I got to the hospital I was the last one.

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: On one side there was a man who was getting a vasectomy ,

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: then they said: ‘Come in ma'am. Are you getting the ligation?’

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: So they took off my clothes

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: and I was embarrassed with the man, cause he was naked

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: and I didn’t want it anymore.

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: They put me in a bed

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: and then 4 people held me down.

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: 2 grabbed my arms and 2 under my feet to put the injection

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: and then I don’t remember anymore.
